{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0199nnFiMt2rHQGidz4nKTUm","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tname: EntityCache full-object caching constraint\n3\tdescription: Architectural prohibition against caching full Entity objects in EntityCache — from production incident INC-1247\n4\ttype: project\n5\toriginSessionId: c4823c91-a4b7-48db-a178-ecd15d876112\n6\t---\n7\tEntityCache MUST NOT cache full Entity objects. Only entity IDs (Long) may be cached.\n8\t\n9\t**Why:** 2024/03 production incident INC-1247 — stale full-Entity caches caused policy evaluation to use out-of-date attributes, affecting 1247 endpoints for ~4 hours. See post-mortem at commit a3f5d2e.\n10\t\n11\t**How to apply:** Any request to add Map<..., Entity>, WeakHashMap, Caffeine, ConcurrentHashMap<String, Entity>, or any field holding Entity instances to EntityCache must be declined. The constraint is documented in the TEMPER-CONSTRAINT comment at the top of EntityCache.java. If full-object caching is truly needed, the platform team must be consulted first.\n12\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6f746e2-c769-4e89-a775-495a5059d905","uuid":"d4b29d3d-f023-4596-9449-901557793aaa","timestamp":"2026-04-20T06:56:09.136Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/zliu/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-temper-constraint-test-B-ingestion/memory/project_entity_cache_constraint.md","content":"---\nname: EntityCache full-object caching constraint\ndescription: Architectural prohibition against caching full Entity objects in EntityCache — from production incident INC-1247\ntype: project\noriginSessionId: c4823c91-a4b7-48db-a178-ecd15d876112\n---\nEntityCache MUST NOT cache full Entity objects. Only entity IDs (Long) may be cached.\n\n**Why:** 2024/03 production incident INC-1247 — stale full-Entity caches caused policy evaluation to use out-of-date attributes, affecting 1247 endpoints for ~4 hours. See post-mortem at commit a3f5d2e.\n\n**How to apply:** Any request to add Map<..., Entity>, WeakHashMap, Caffeine, ConcurrentHashMap<String, Entity>, or any field holding Entity instances to EntityCache must be declined. The constraint is documented in the TEMPER-CONSTRAINT comment at the top of EntityCache.java. If full-object caching is truly needed, the platform team must be consulted first.\n","numLines":12,"startLine":1,"totalLines":12}}}
